-- models/intermediate/int_product_categories.sql
```sql
-- Join products with categories, handle missing categories
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        p.product_id,
        p.name AS product_name,
        c.name AS category_name
    FROM {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
)
SELECT
    product_id,
    product_name,
    COALESCE(category_name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/mart/fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Calculate return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        pc.category_name,
        oi.item_id,
        dr.item_id AS returned_item_id
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_product_categories') }} pc
        ON pc.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} dr
        ON dr.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold,
    COUNT(returned_item_id) AS total_items_returned,
    CAST(COUNT(returned_item_id) AS DECIMAL(10,2)) / NULLIF(COUNT(*), 0) AS return_rate
FROM source
GROUP BY category_name
